Emulate RPi screen on laptop:

- create ssh tunnel btw RPi and laptop (with ethernet cable):
	- branch ethernet cable
	- get RPi's IP with 'arp-scan -l' command
	- create ssh tunnel 'ssh pi@<rpi-ip>'
- use SSL/SSH vnc server:
	- in the RPi terminal ssh-connected, type 'vncserver'
	- open SSL/SSH VNC Viewer and choose SSH
	- VNC Host/Display : 'pi@<rpi-ip>:1 and click on connect
	- enter RPi password
	- enter VNC password

source : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NUHRhNB67F4
